Photomagick ver 1.x

Copyright (c) Karol BÄ™dkowski, 2011

Stupid, small application for modifying photos by apply pre-defined filters.


Prohtomagix is written in Python, wxWidgets and PIL, so it should be portable
and possible to run in every environment supported by this software.

Application work in two main modes:
- command line - allow to batch processing selected images
- gui - allow to apply some filters and see result

In GUI-mode, there are three available options:
- simple - allow to use predefined, "main" filters
- advanced - allow to choice three filters: style, modificator and decorator
- expert - allow to choice any combination of all available filters.


Requirements:
- Python 2.6
- wxPython 2.8.x (python-wxgtk2.8)
- Python Imaging Library (PIL) 1.1.7+  (python-imaging)
Optional:
- Python and PIL headers and C compiler for compiling optional supporting modules.


